android.permission.INTERNET.description: Allows an application to create network sockets.

android.permission.ACCESS_WIFI_STATE.description: Allows an application to view the information about the status of Wi-Fi.

android.permission.USE_CREDENTIALS.info: use the authentication credentials of an account
android.permission.USE_CREDENTIALS.description: Allows an application to request authentication tokens.

android.permission.WAKE_LOCK.description: Allows an application to prevent the phone from going to sleep.

android.permission.ACCESS_COARSE_LOCATIO.description: Access coarse location sources, such as the mobile network database, to determine an approximate phone location, where available. Malicious applications can use this to determine approximately where you are.

android.permission.RECEIVE_BOOT_COMPLETE.description: Allows an application to start itself as soon as the system has finished booting. This can make it take longer to start the phone and allow the application to slow down the overall phone by always running.

android.permission.USE_FINGERPRINT.description: This constant was deprecated in API level 28. Applications should request USE_BIOMETRIC instead.

android.permission.AUTHENTICATE_ACCOUNTS.description: Allows an application to use the account authenticator capabilities of the Account Manager, including creating accounts as well as obtaining and setting their passwords.

android.permission.ACCESS_NETWORK_STATE.description: Allows an application to view the status of all networks.

android.permission.VIBRATE.description: Allows the application to control the vibrator.

android.permission.POST_NOTIFICATIONS.info: allows an app to post notifications.
android.permission.POST_NOTIFICATIONS.description: Allows an app to post notifications

com.google.android.gms.permission.AD_ID.description: This app uses a Google advertising ID and can possibly serve advertisements.

android.permission.ACCESS_ADSERVICES_AD_.info: allow app to access the device's advertising ID.
android.permission.ACCESS_ADSERVICES_AD_.description: This ID is a unique, user-resettable identifier provided by Google's advertising services, allowing apps to track user behavior for advertising purposes while maintaining user privacy.

android.permission.ACCESS_ADSERVICES_ATT.info: allow applications to access advertising service attribution
android.permission.ACCESS_ADSERVICES_ATT.description: This enables the app to retrieve information related to advertising attribution, which can be used for targeted advertising purposes. App can gather data about how users interact with ads, such as clicks or impressions, to measure the effectiveness of advertising campaigns.

android.permission.ACCESS_ADSERVICES_TOP.info: allow applications to access advertising service topics
android.permission.ACCESS_ADSERVICES_TOP.description: This enables the app to retrieve information related to advertising topics or interests, which can be used for targeted advertising purposes.

android.permission.FOREGROUND_SERVICE.info: enables regular apps to use Service.startForeground.
android.permission.FOREGROUND_SERVICE.description: Allows a regular application to use Service.startForeground.

android.permission.WRITE_EXTERNAL_STORAG.description: Allows an application to write to external storage.

com.google.android.c2dm.permission.RECEI.description: Allows an application to receive push notifications from cloud.

android.permission.USE_BIOMETRIC.info: allows use of device-supported biometric modalities.
android.permission.USE_BIOMETRIC.description: Allows an app to use device supported biometric modalities.

com.google.android.finsky.permission.BIN.description: A custom permission defined by Google.

nx.description: The binary has NX bit set. This marks a memory page non-executable making attacker injected shellcode non-executable.

pie.description: The shared object is build with -fPIC flag which enables Position independent code. This makes Return Oriented Programming (ROP) attacks much more difficult to execute reliably.

stack_canary.description: This binary has a stack canary value added to the stack so that it will be overwritten by a stack buffer that overflows the return address. This allows detection of overflows by verifying the integrity of the canary before function return.

relocation_readonly.description: This shared object has full RELRO enabled. RELRO ensures that the GOT cannot be overwritten in vulnerable ELF binaries. In Full RELRO, the entire GOT (.got and .got.plt both) is marked as read-only.

metadata.cwe: CWE-312: Cleartext Storage of Sensitive Information
metadata.description: Files may contain hardcoded sensitive information like usernames, passwords, keys etc.
This App uses SSL certificate pinning to detect or  prevent MITM attacks in secure communication channel.

metadata.cwe: CWE-532: Insertion of Sensitive Information into Log File
metadata.description: The App logs information. Sensitive information should never be logged.

metadata.cwe: CWE-89: Improper Neutralization of Special Elements used in an SQL Command ('SQL Injection')
metadata.description: App uses SQLite Database and execute raw SQL query. Untrusted user input in raw SQL queries can cause SQL Injection. Also sensitive information should be encrypted and written to the database.
This App copies data to clipboard. Sensitive data should not be copied to clipboard as other applications can access it.
IP Address disclosure

metadata.description: SHA-1 is a weak hash known to have hash collisions.
App creates temp file. Sensitive information should never be written into a temp file.

metadata.description: MD5 is a weak hash known to have hash collisions.

"ovulation_test_modal" : "How they work

Ovulation tests work by detecting a surge in LH (luteinizing hormone) that comes right before ovulation. A positive test means that an egg is about to be released in the next 24-36 hours.

When to take

Though everyone is different, ovulation occurs at about 14 days before your next expected period. For the most accurate results, it's recommended to start testing 16-17 days before your next expected period.

How to read your results

Reading the results of your ovulation test depends on the type of test. With test strips, you'll know you're about to ovulate if the test line shows up as dark or darker than the control line. If you're using a digital ovulation test, you'll get a clear readout on the display telling you whether you're ovulating."

"vaginal_bleeding_discharge_modal" : "Lochia is the bleeding and discharge that happens after birth. It comes from where your placenta was once attached to your uterus. It usually begins as heavy, red bleeding that changes over time to pink or brown in color. This then becomes a heavy white discharge and then stops. This process can last up to six weeks and is a natural part of the healing process.

While it is normal to pass some clots, if you notice many or large clots along with increased fresh red bleeding, contact your healthcare provider."

"vaginal_delivery_recovery_modal" : "Después de un parto vaginal, haz aquí un seguimiento de tu curación.

Es frecuente que aparezca dolor, ardor, comezón o hinchazón. Se producen alrededor de la vagina (canal del parto), la vulva (genitales externos) y el perineo (entre la vagina y el recto). Normalmente empiezan a aliviarse en los primeros días y desaparecen en unas semanas. Pero pueden durar más si tienes desgarros. También pueden producirse hemorroides (vasos sanguíneos hinchados alrededor del recto) y escapes de orina.

La incontinencia fecal, es decir, no poder retener la deposición, es más probable tras un parto asistido o un desgarro cerca del ano. Esto puede mejorar de forma natural o requerir tratamiento. Por lo que es importante que le informes a tu médico si experimentas esto."

"post_delivery_cramps_modal" : "Cramps after birth, sometimes called “after pains,” are a normal part of recovery.

During pregnancy, your uterus grew large enough to hold your baby, placenta, and amniotic fluid. Now, it must shrink back down. Cramping is part of that process.

It’s common to feel cramps while breastfeeding because the same hormone that lets down breast milk (oxytocin) also tells your uterus to contract. These “after pains” are usually most intense in the first few days after birth and get better with time."

"vaginal_delivery_recovery_modal" : "After a vaginal birth, track your healing here.

Pain, burning, itching, or swelling are common. They occur around the vagina (birth canal), vulva (external genitals) and perineum (between the vagina and rectum). They typically start to ease in the first few days and go away in a few weeks. But, they may last longer if you have tearing. Hemorrhoids (swollen blood vessels around your rectum) and urine leakage can also happen.

Fecal incontinence, being unable to hold a bowel movement, is more likely after assisted birth or tearing near the anus. This may improve naturally or require treatment. So, it's important to inform your provider if you are experiencing this."

"pregnancy_test_modal" : "How they work

Pregnancy tests detect hCG (human chorionic gonadotropin), a hormone that your body produces during pregnancy.

When to take

You can take a pregnancy test up to five days before you expect your next period, but for the most accurate results, it's best to wait until the date of your missed period and use the first urine of the day.

How to read your results

The method of reading the results varies among tests. With most test strips and non-digital tests, two lines mean positive, and one line is negative. With digital tests, the display screen will typically read "pregnant/not pregnant," "yes/no," or have some sort of symbol indicating a positive or negative."

"ovulation_test_modal" : "Cómo funcionan

Las pruebas de ovulación funcionan detectando un aumento de LH (hormona luteinizante) que se produce justo antes de la ovulación. Un test positivo significa que un óvulo está a punto de ser liberado en las próximas 24-36 horas.

Cuándo hacerse la prueba

Aunque cada persona es diferente, la ovulación se produce aproximadamente 14 días antes del siguiente periodo previsto. Para obtener los resultados más precisos, se recomienda empezar a realizar la prueba 16-17 días antes del siguiente periodo previsto.

Cómo leer tus resultados

La lectura de los resultados de la prueba de ovulación depende del tipo de prueba. Con las tiras reactivas, sabrás que estás a punto de ovular si la línea de la prueba se muestra oscura o más oscura que la línea de control. Si utilizas una prueba de ovulación digital, obtendrás una lectura clara en la pantalla que te indicará si estás ovulando."

"pregnancy_test_modal" : "Cómo funcionan

Las pruebas de embarazo detectan la hCG (gonadotropina coriónica humana), una hormona que el cuerpo produce durante el embarazo.

Cuándo hacerse la prueba

Puedes hacerte una prueba de embarazo hasta cinco días antes de la fecha en que esperas tener la siguiente menstruación, pero para obtener resultados más precisos, es mejor esperar hasta la fecha de la falta de tu menstruación y utilizar la primera orina del día.

Cómo leer tus resultados

El método de lectura de los resultados varía según las pruebas. Con la mayoría de las tiras reactivas y las pruebas no digitales, dos líneas significan positivo y una línea es negativa. Con las pruebas digitales, la pantalla suele decir "pregnant/not pregnant"  ("embarazada/no embarazada"), "sí/no" o tener algún tipo de símbolo que indique un resultado positivo o negativo."

playstore_details.title: Ovia Cycle & Pregnancy Tracker
playstore_details.description:
At Ovia Health by Labcorp, we’re here to empower women with personalized tools and data-driven insights that support every stage of their health journey—helping them make informed decisions and get the care they need.
Whether you're tracking your period, trying to get pregnant, monitoring your pregnancy, or tracking your health, join the millions of Ovia users.

Voted one of the best pregnancy and fertility tracker apps, Ovia helps you stay on top of all your women’s health needs—tracking your pregnancy, menstrual cycle , period and ovulation predictions, postpartum recovery, perimenopause symptoms, menopause support, and overall wellness, all in one place!

YOUR HEALTH IN YOUR HANDS
◆ Personalized email summaries and reminders to help you make the most of your experience and manage your health
◆ Period & Fertility calendar - Fertility forecasting algorithm predicts your fertility widows and ovulation cycles.
◆ Pregnancy - Baby growth calendar, due date countdown, bump and fetal movement tracker, and more. Watch your baby grow, track your symptoms, and learn what to expect each week.
◆ Postpartum Experience - personalized recovery modes based on delivery (vaginal, c-section, VBAC), symptom tracking, and more.
◆ Perimenopause & Menopause support - comprehensive health tracking for real-time alerts & personalized feedback.
◆ Access over 2,000 free expert articles on fertility, ovulation, conception, postpartum, menopause & reproductive health.

OVULATION CALCULATOR & FERTILITY TRACKER
◆ Fertile window and ovulation time predictions and a daily fertility score. An ovulation app that helps you know when you’re ovulating when trying to conceive (TTC).


PERIOD AND MENSTRUAL CYCLE TRACKER
◆ A period tracker with customizable data logging inclusive of symptoms, moods, sex, and nutrition.
◆ Support for regular & irregular menstrual cycles.
◆ Birth control tracking

PREGNANCY & POSTPARTUM
◆ A personalized, 12-month program focused on birth recovery, postpartum conditions and complications, reproductive planning, return to work support, mental health, & more.

PERIMENOPAUSE & MENOPAUSE SUPPORT
◆ Symptom tracking, education, and support to navigate perimenopause & menopause confidently.

STAY UP TO DATE ON YOUR PREGNANCY WITH ESSENTIALS
◆ Pregnancy Week by Week: Know what to expect each week with a baby due date countdown and weekly videos and content about pregnancy symptoms, body changes, & baby tips.
◆ Pregnancy Tracker and Baby Growth Calendar: Compare your baby’s weekly size to a fruit, toy, pastry item, or animal. View 3D illustrations of your baby each week & track baby’s growth.
◆ My Baby Names: Swipe through thousands of baby names. Save your favorites.
◆ Baby Hand and Foot Size: See a life-size image of how big your baby's hands and feet are today compared to how big they'll be at your due date!
◆ Bump Tracker: Keep a record of your growing baby bump in countdown.
◆ Safety Lookup Tools: Use lookup tools for symptoms & food safety.
◆ Kick Counter & Contraction Timer: Count baby kicks & contractions as your due date approaches.

OTHER FEATURES OUR MEMBERS LOVE
◆ Friends & Family Sharing: Add your spouse, partner, sibling, or your BFF to share your daily updates.
◆ Privacy and Security: Add an extra layer of protection by adding a PIN to your account.
◆ Apple Health & Fitbit Integrations: Share data from Ovia to the Apple Health app. Sync your Fitbit to share steps, sleep & weight with Ovia.

OVIA HEALTH BY LABCORP
Ovia Health by Labcorp is the leading digital health companion for women across their entire health journey, from general and preventive health through perimenopause and menopause.
Have Ovia Health by Labcorp through your employer or health plan? Download the app, enter your plan info, and access premium tools like health coaching, personalized content, and programs for birth control tracking, endometriosis, PCOS, & more.

CUSTOMER SERVICE
We're always working to improve your experience. Email us: support@oviahealth.com

hotspot.title: Found 5 critical permission(s)
hotspot.description:
Ensure that these permissions are required by the application.

android.permission.USE_CREDENTIALS (dangerous): use the authentication credentials of an account - Allows an application to request authentication tokens.

android.permission.ACCESS_COARSE_LOCATION (dangerous): coarse (network-based) location - Access coarse location sources, such as the mobile network database, to determine an approximate phone location, where available. Malicious applications can use this to determine approximately where you are.

android.permission.AUTHENTICATE_ACCOUNTS (dangerous): act as an account authenticator - Allows an application to use the account authenticator capabilities of the Account Manager, including creating accounts as well as obtaining and setting their passwords.

android.permission.POST_NOTIFICATIONS (dangerous): allows an app to post notifications. - Allows an app to post notifications

android.permission.WRITE_EXTERNAL_STORAGE (dangerous): read/modify/delete external storage contents - Allows an application to write to external storage.
